title: Start
---
<<declare $trust = 0>>
<<declare $knows_secret = false>>

You encounter a mysterious traveler at the crossroads.

$c1: Greetings, wanderer. These roads can be dangerous alone.

$c1: I can point out the dangerous road without walking it for you.
-> $c2: Greet them warmly
    <<set $trust += 1>>
    $c2: Hello there! It's good to see a friendly face.
    $c1: Indeed it is. Perhaps we could travel together a while?
    <<jump TravelTogether>>
-> $c2: Eye them suspiciously
    $c2: I can handle myself just fine.
    $c1: I'm sure you can. But even the strongest benefit from allies.
    <<jump Suspicious>>
-> $c2: Ignore them and walk past
    You walk past without a word.
    $c1: Suit yourself... but beware the bridge ahead.
    <<jump Alone>>
===
title: TravelTogether
---
You walk together down the winding path.

$c1: I should warn you—there's trouble at the old bridge.

-> $c2: Ask for details
    <<set $trust += 1>>
    $c1: Bandits have been collecting "tolls." Unfair ones.
    <<if $trust >= 2>>
        $c1: I know a secret path, if you're interested...
        <<set $knows_secret to true>>
        <<jump SecretPath>>
    <<else>>
        $c1: But together, we might get through.
        <<jump Bridge>>
    <<endif>>
-> $c2: Say nothing
    <<jump Bridge>>
===
title: Suspicious
---
$c1: I understand caution. The world has earned it.

They reach into their cloak. You tense.

But they only pull out a worn map.

$c1: Here—take this. It shows a path around the bandits at the bridge.

-> $c2: Accept the map
    <<set $knows_secret to true>>
    $c2: Thank you. I... misjudged you.
    $c1: Safe travels.
    <<jump SecretPath>>
-> $c2: Refuse
    $c2: I don't need help.
    <<jump Bridge>>
===
title: Alone
---
You continue alone.

The bridge looms ahead, three figures waiting in the shadows.

<<jump Bridge>>
===
title: SecretPath
---
Following the hidden path, you bypass the bridge entirely.

The forest is quiet here. Peaceful.

You emerge safely on the other side, grateful for the unexpected help.

// Continue your story here!
===
title: Bridge
---
The bridge bandits block your path.

<<if $trust >= 1>>
    But you're not alone.
    $c1: Let us pass, or face us both.
    The bandits reconsider and step aside.
<<else>>
    Bandit: Toll's ten gold. Or we take your pack.
    -> $c2: Pay the toll
        You hand over the coins reluctantly.
    -> $c2: Fight!
        It's a tough fight, but you prevail.
<<endif>>

You cross the bridge and continue your journey.

// Continue your story here!
===
